            <div class="section">
                <div class="section-title"><span class="num">1</span> Background & Problem Statement</div>
                <div class="card-grid">
                    <div class="card"><h3>📌 Current User Journey</h3><p>Professionals, students, and entrepreneurs create 2~4 PPTs per month on average. When using AI assistance today, the typical workflow is:<br>① Open browser → cloud tools like Doubao/DeepSeek;<br>② Iteratively prompt to adjust outline and content;<br>③ Download file to local;<br>④ Manually fix formatting and supplement local assets.<br><strong>The process is fragmented, inefficient, and uploading sensitive data to the cloud poses privacy risks.</strong></p></div>
                    <div class="card"><h3>🔥 Core Pain Points</h3><ul><li><strong>Awareness Barrier</strong>: Many ordinary users don't know AI can create PPTs, remaining unreached.</li><li><strong>Fragmented Operations</strong>: Constant switching among browser, local app, and file manager.</li><li><strong>Privacy Leakage</strong>: Business plans, internal data uploaded to third-party cloud, high compliance risk.</li><li><strong>Wasted Local Assets</strong>: Existing memos, Word outlines, Markdown notes cannot be automatically turned into slides.</li><li><strong>Offline Unavailable</strong>: Completely unusable on flights, high-speed trains, or outdoors without internet.</li></ul></div>
                </div>
